Recently went to Mississauga to grab a fabi foosball table for a friend - while out on the west side of town decided to try out a few places to eat. One spot I checked was @pizzakarachi which was recommended by one of my colleagues.

The Pizza stores indicates where Italy meets Karachi - definitely a good summary of the tastes within the Pizza.

I order the Ghost Kohr which is similar to a meat lovers pizza with beef pepperoni, beef salami, chicken tikka, minced beef, hot peppers and special cheese blend.

The one I enjoyed the most was the Bihari Chaska - which is basically a kebab Pizza with bihari sauce, chilli, peppers and a special cheese mix. This one was definitely something I never tasted before - it's Pakistani flavours on a pizza which meshed very well - spicy, sweet and savoury all in one bite.
